The presidential candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in the 2023 general elections, former Vice President Atiku Abubakar, has sustained his mobilization for the unity of the PDP towards the 2023 presidential election after the party’s national convention in Abuja.
Atiku, after receiving his Certificate of Return at the PDP National Secretariat, Abuja, on Wednesday acknowledged the love and unity PDP Governors, PDP leaders, party supporters, stakeholders and other presidential aspirants have shown through the nomination processes, including the consultation period unto the convention.
The PDP presidential candidate in a tweet on his official twitter handle Atiku Abubakar @atiku, wrote: I thank all for “The love and unity shown by Governors of our great party, the @OfficialPDPNig, my worthy co-aspirants, the NWC, our leaders past and present, stakeholders and party faithful and supporters at the collection of my Certificate of Return as the PDP presidential candidate.”
Atiku at the PDP secretariat on Wednesday received his Certificate of Return as the party’s candidate for the 2023 presidential race. The former Vice President commended all party stakeholders, assuring Nigerians that he would put an end to the misrule of the All Progressives Congress (APC) government in the past seven years.
Atiku had earlier reeled out his five cardinal policies to rescue and restore the lost glory of Nigeria in the areas of education, economy, security, national unity, etc.
 
